19
00:00:18,606 --> 00:00:20,483
<i>Fugitives on the run!</i>

20
00:00:20,566 --> 00:00:23,236
<i>Disguised as Jedi killer, Rako Hardeen,</i>

21
00:00:23,277 --> 00:00:25,238
<i>Obi-Wan Kenobi works undercover</i>

22
00:00:25,279 --> 00:00:28,449
<i>to solve a Separatist plot
against Chancellor Palpatine.</i>

23
00:00:28,783 --> 00:00:32,328
<i>Obi-Wan meets the plot's mastermind,
Moralo Eval,</i>

24
00:00:32,411 --> 00:00:35,122
<i>breaking him out of jail to gain his trust.</i>

25
00:00:35,206 --> 00:00:38,042
<i>But now, Kenobi faces another obstacle,</i>

26
00:00:38,125 --> 00:00:40,211
<i>bounty hunter, Cad Bane.</i>

27
00:00:40,628 --> 00:00:43,881
<i>Can Obi-Wan Kenobi
overcome Bane's suspicions?</i>

28
00:00:43,965 --> 00:00:46,801
<i>Or will the ruthless criminal
see through his disguise</i>

29
00:00:46,926 --> 00:00:48,344
<i>and expose the Jedi?</i>

30
00:00:48,594 --> 00:00:50,263
<i>Only time will tell.</i>

31
00:00:52,014 --> 00:00:54,225
We're coming in too fast, Hardeen.

32
00:00:54,308 --> 00:00:55,476
Are you trying to kill us?

33
00:00:55,810 --> 00:00:58,145
They'll be waiting for us
at every space port.

34
00:00:58,229 --> 00:00:59,647
We have to ditch the ship.

35
00:01:01,816 --> 00:01:04,694
You mean you're going
to intentionally crash us into the swamp?

36
00:01:04,986 --> 00:01:07,905
Yeah, that is exactly what I'm gonna do.

37
00:01:07,989 --> 00:01:10,491
He's right. We have no choice.

38
00:01:10,825 --> 00:01:12,785
Get ready for a fast exit.

39
00:01:54,535 --> 00:01:57,747
Nobody can trace us here.
The swamp will swallow up the ship.

40
00:01:58,372 --> 00:02:01,292
So we leave no trace of our crash.

41
00:02:01,375 --> 00:02:04,962
Moralo Eval likes a man who plans ahead.

42
00:02:09,634 --> 00:02:12,136
You do have a plan?

43
00:02:12,720 --> 00:02:15,306
Yeah, I know Nal Hutta.

44
00:02:15,389 --> 00:02:18,017
We can get a new ship
at the Bilbousa Bazaar,

45
00:02:18,059 --> 00:02:20,061
but this time, we buy one.

46
00:02:20,102 --> 00:02:22,897
Otherwise, we'll have the authorities
back on our tail.

47
00:02:23,272 --> 00:02:24,649
Not so fast.

48
00:02:24,732 --> 00:02:27,526
We need to ditch these prison fatigues.

49
00:02:27,568 --> 00:02:30,237
We'll have a bounty on our heads
for escaping

50
00:02:30,279 --> 00:02:33,032
and I don't like to stand out.

51
00:02:52,551 --> 00:02:54,637
That's local security.

52
00:02:54,720 --> 00:02:56,514
Keep moving.

53
00:03:04,939 --> 00:03:07,316
We'll get some new gear and equipment.

54
00:03:07,733 --> 00:03:09,777
Pablo's pawn shop

55
00:03:09,860 --> 00:03:13,280
has everything a bounty hunter needs
and more.

56
00:03:27,712 --> 00:03:30,047
Now all I need's a new hat.

57
00:03:35,594 --> 00:03:36,679
For trying to blend in,

58
00:03:36,762 --> 00:03:39,181
your hat sure makes you stand out.

59
00:03:41,058 --> 00:03:43,602
I don't like to hide under a helmet.

60
00:03:44,687 --> 00:03:48,774
Is there anything else you desire?
A new ship?

61
00:03:48,816 --> 00:03:51,986
Your choice of weapons is lousy, Pablo.

62
00:03:52,069 --> 00:03:54,530
Where can I get some quality blasters?

63
00:03:54,989 --> 00:03:59,201
I wouldn't be too picky being on the run,
like you obviously are.

64
00:04:02,455 --> 00:04:05,750
I'd keep my mouth shut if I were you, Pablo.

65
00:04:05,833 --> 00:04:08,210
We'll get our weapons elsewhere.

66
00:04:10,337 --> 00:04:12,047
Thanks for the hat.

67
00:04:13,382 --> 00:04:14,633
For your trouble.

68
00:04:21,223 --> 00:04:23,893
That trader's heard worse threats
than yours, Bane.

69
00:04:23,976 --> 00:04:25,686
Probably calling the Hutts right now,

70
00:04:25,728 --> 00:04:27,188
seeing what kind of bounty there is on us.

71
00:04:32,777 --> 00:04:33,903
Relax.

72
00:04:34,320 --> 00:04:37,364
On this slime-pool, everybody's an outlaw.

73
00:04:37,615 --> 00:04:40,409
Besides, they'll be looking for three of us.

74
00:04:40,493 --> 00:04:41,577
So we're splitting up.

75
00:04:42,036 --> 00:04:44,538
You find a ship, we'll get weapons.

76
00:04:45,873 --> 00:04:47,541
Not so fast.

77
00:04:47,666 --> 00:04:51,128
If it's all the same to you,
I'll get the weapons.

78
00:04:51,212 --> 00:04:53,380
It's not the same to me.

79
00:04:53,422 --> 00:04:56,675
You crashed the ship,
you get us a new one.

80
00:05:00,554 --> 00:05:02,807
It does seem fair.

81
00:05:07,603 --> 00:05:10,648
Soon as we have a ship, we ditch Hardeen.

82
00:05:11,273 --> 00:05:12,566
Really?

83
00:05:12,733 --> 00:05:14,235
We'll throw him to the Hutts.

84
00:05:14,276 --> 00:05:17,238
While they interrogate him,
we'll be long gone.

85
00:05:18,155 --> 00:05:22,326
Tell me, is this business or personal?

86
00:05:24,286 --> 00:05:25,746
Both.

87
00:05:37,758 --> 00:05:39,760
No, no, no. That's my final offer.

88
00:05:51,230 --> 00:05:53,607
All right then, it's a deal.

89
00:05:53,649 --> 00:05:54,859
Good timing.

90
00:05:54,942 --> 00:05:57,236
Soon as you pay for the ship,
we can get moving.

91
00:05:57,278 --> 00:05:59,113
With pleasure.

92
00:06:00,364 --> 00:06:01,907
Hey, where's my weapon?

93
00:06:02,324 --> 00:06:04,952
Won't need it. You're not coming.

94
00:06:05,244 --> 00:06:06,495
Says who?

95
00:06:07,621 --> 00:06:12,001
He doesn't want to split his fee
for breaking me out of prison.

96
00:06:12,084 --> 00:06:15,129
And also, he despises you.

97
00:06:16,338 --> 00:06:19,717
All I know is I'm not going anywhere
without my reward.

98
00:06:19,800 --> 00:06:23,012
I'm sorry. This is between you two.

99
00:06:24,013 --> 00:06:26,015
What's it gonna be, Bane?

100
00:06:32,980 --> 00:06:34,815
Here's your reward,

101
00:06:34,857 --> 00:06:37,318
I'm not killing you.

102
00:06:58,839 --> 00:06:59,924
Where am I?

103
00:07:01,508 --> 00:07:03,886
You're a guest of the Hutts.

104
00:07:03,969 --> 00:07:07,973
If you do not answer my questions
about your two partners,

105
00:07:09,600 --> 00:07:12,144
we will not be so hospitable.

106
00:07:17,191 --> 00:07:19,193
You call this hospitable?

107
00:07:20,736 --> 00:07:23,072
Wait. Torture won't be necessary.

108
00:07:23,155 --> 00:07:24,823
My partners double-crossed me,

109
00:07:25,574 --> 00:07:27,785
but I put a tracking device on their ship.

110
00:07:28,035 --> 00:07:30,996
Let me down and I'll tell you the frequency.

111
00:07:35,793 --> 00:07:39,380
Now tell us the tracking frequency.

112
00:07:45,344 --> 00:07:48,847
Yes, Count Dooku. I'm sorry I was delayed.

113
00:07:48,931 --> 00:07:50,182
I'm free now.

114
00:07:50,224 --> 00:07:53,018
I'll try to reach Serenno
as soon as possible.

115
00:07:53,477 --> 00:07:55,729
<i>No more excuses, Eval.</i>

116
00:07:55,813 --> 00:07:58,148
<i>Time is running short.</i>

117
00:07:58,232 --> 00:08:01,443
Yes, Count Dooku, no more excuses.

118
00:08:03,404 --> 00:08:05,322
You said it yourself, Eval.

119
00:08:05,406 --> 00:08:08,867
You're free now. I want my money.

120
00:08:08,909 --> 00:08:13,414
After the weapons and the ship,
I have very few credits left.

121
00:08:13,539 --> 00:08:16,250
You'll be paid when we reach Serenno.

122
00:08:20,921 --> 00:08:22,840
What is this? Who is attacking us?

123
00:08:23,298 --> 00:08:24,633
The Hutts!

124
00:08:24,758 --> 00:08:26,552
How did they find us so quickly?

125
00:08:26,844 --> 00:08:29,763
Hardeen, trying to even the score.

126
00:08:33,142 --> 00:08:35,936
The engines are fried,
we'll have to turn back.

127
00:08:42,443 --> 00:08:45,112
<i>Their ship will crash soon on Nal Hutta.</i>

128
00:08:45,154 --> 00:08:47,614
<i>Be there to capture the fugitives.</i>

129
00:08:50,451 --> 00:08:52,286
You found the ship like I said.

130
00:08:54,371 --> 00:08:56,331
Our deal was you'd let me go now.

131
00:08:56,415 --> 00:08:59,460
The deal has changed.

132
00:09:44,088 --> 00:09:45,339
This is Ben.

133
00:09:45,380 --> 00:09:47,299
I apologize
for being out of communication,

134
00:09:47,341 --> 00:09:50,135
but the situation was rather tenuous.

135
00:09:50,844 --> 00:09:54,389
Although, it now appears
things may be on track soon.

136
00:09:54,473 --> 00:09:55,724
<i>Here's what I need,</i>

137
00:09:55,808 --> 00:09:57,476
<i>have the bounty on us removed.</i>

138
00:09:57,518 --> 00:09:59,394
<i>If I can win over Cad Bane,</i>

139
00:09:59,478 --> 00:10:01,563
<i>I can learn more about Eval's plot.</i>

140
00:10:01,855 --> 00:10:04,358
<i>But there can be no more complications.</i>

141
00:10:04,525 --> 00:10:06,944
<i>So no matter what reports you hear,</i>

142
00:10:07,027 --> 00:10:09,071
<i>do not contact me or send help.</i>

143
00:10:11,198 --> 00:10:13,283
<i>And one more thing,</i>

144
00:10:13,367 --> 00:10:15,536
<i>I shall need enough credits
to buy a new ship.</i>

145
00:10:19,873 --> 00:10:23,085
Why are you removing the bounty
on the three fugitives?

146
00:10:23,168 --> 00:10:26,421
<i>If they're free to move,
they could lead us back to Eval's operation.</i>

147
00:10:26,880 --> 00:10:29,383
Very well. Keep me apprised.

148
00:10:31,760 --> 00:10:33,804
You look troubled, Anakin.

149
00:10:35,389 --> 00:10:38,058
How can they expect me to just sit here
and do nothing

150
00:10:38,142 --> 00:10:40,477
with Obi-Wan's murderer on the loose?

151
00:10:40,561 --> 00:10:45,065
It is possible that they do not trust you
to control your feelings.

152
00:10:46,900 --> 00:10:50,112
Hardeen killed my master, my best friend!

153
00:10:50,988 --> 00:10:53,866
And now he's escaping with Cad Bane
and Moralo Eval,

154
00:10:53,907 --> 00:10:57,411
and the Jedi Council won't do anything
about it!

155
00:10:57,494 --> 00:11:02,082
I have it from a reliable source
that the fugitives were last headed

156
00:11:02,249 --> 00:11:04,501
towards Nal Hutta.

157
00:11:05,586 --> 00:11:08,297
You cannot deny your feelings, Anakin.

158
00:11:08,630 --> 00:11:10,924
They are what make you special.

159
00:11:12,301 --> 00:11:16,138
If you believe you can stop this plot
against me,

160
00:11:16,221 --> 00:11:17,848
I trust you.

161
00:11:18,599 --> 00:11:21,393
Thank you, Chancellor.
You won't regret this.

162
00:11:23,687 --> 00:11:25,731
No. I won't.

163
00:11:29,735 --> 00:11:32,279
Oh, back so soon?

164
00:11:39,244 --> 00:11:41,371
Let me guess? You missed me?

165
00:11:44,875 --> 00:11:45,876
Watch it!

166
00:11:46,585 --> 00:11:49,338
Kill me and you won't get off Nal Hutta.

167
00:11:49,630 --> 00:11:53,884
Moralo Eval is running out of time
and patience.

168
00:11:54,176 --> 00:11:56,303
Let the man talk.

169
00:11:59,848 --> 00:12:01,725
Look, I've got a ship.

170
00:12:01,808 --> 00:12:06,313
You've got the Hutts on your tail,
so you make me a partner in everything.

171
00:12:07,648 --> 00:12:09,942
Your deal is accepted.

172
00:12:11,026 --> 00:12:12,152
No.

173
00:12:12,819 --> 00:12:16,823
First I wanna know
where you got the credits to buy a ship?

174
00:12:17,324 --> 00:12:19,493
You thought you left me for dead,

175
00:12:19,534 --> 00:12:21,328
but the Hutts owed me a favor.

176
00:12:21,495 --> 00:12:24,164
So you had them shoot us down?

177
00:12:24,248 --> 00:12:26,500
You would've done the same thing, Bane.

178
00:12:26,583 --> 00:12:28,961
The way I see it, we're even now.

179
00:12:29,419 --> 00:12:31,505
Now that we're all friends,

180
00:12:31,630 --> 00:12:35,008
get me off this festering stink-hole.

181
00:12:38,679 --> 00:12:41,390
Wait, who's going to pay for this mess?

182
00:12:45,894 --> 00:12:51,024
So about your fee from Eval,
a 50I50 split sounds fair to me.

183
00:12:51,108 --> 00:12:53,860
Over my dead corpse.

184
00:12:53,902 --> 00:12:55,445
Don't tempt me.

185
00:13:05,872 --> 00:13:08,917
What makes you think Obi-Wan's murderer
is on Nal Hutta?

186
00:13:09,001 --> 00:13:11,712
I got a tip from the Chancellor himself.

187
00:13:14,548 --> 00:13:16,008
How are we gonna find them?

188
00:13:16,049 --> 00:13:18,218
Ahsoka, you should know by now.

189
00:13:18,260 --> 00:13:20,095
If you want to find a lowlife...

190
00:13:20,178 --> 00:13:22,389
You start at the saloon.

191
00:13:31,231 --> 00:13:35,152
Hey, ladies, where are we going next?

192
00:13:35,861 --> 00:13:37,654
I love you guys.

193
00:13:56,048 --> 00:13:58,383
The fugitives are already gone.

194
00:13:58,467 --> 00:13:59,843
All three of them were here?

195
00:14:00,552 --> 00:14:02,262
Two came in, met the third.

196
00:14:02,596 --> 00:14:03,764
When did they leave?

197
00:14:04,639 --> 00:14:08,352
Nothing's free on Nal Hutta,
especially information.

198
00:14:08,435 --> 00:14:10,520
I don't have time for games.

199
00:14:10,604 --> 00:14:13,190
You just missed them.

200
00:14:13,940 --> 00:14:15,025
Keep talking.

201
00:14:15,484 --> 00:14:18,612
I heard one of them say
they just bought a ship.

202
00:14:21,114 --> 00:14:22,699
Let's go, Snips.

203
00:14:31,208 --> 00:14:33,835
<i>Captain Rex, I need to speak
with General Skywalker.</i>

204
00:14:33,919 --> 00:14:35,462
<i>He's not responding to my calls.</i>

205
00:14:35,879 --> 00:14:38,799
Sir, General Skywalker is unavailable.

206
00:14:39,341 --> 00:14:40,759
<i>Where is he, Captain?</i>

207
00:14:40,801 --> 00:14:42,844
I can't say, sir.

208
00:14:42,928 --> 00:14:45,639
<i>You can't or you won't?</i>

209
00:14:45,680 --> 00:14:47,974
Anakin is on Nal Hutta.

210
00:14:48,850 --> 00:14:50,185
<i>Nal Hutta?</i>

211
00:14:50,268 --> 00:14:52,604
Protecting me
is only postponing the problem,

212
00:14:52,646 --> 00:14:54,022
not solving it.

213
00:14:54,398 --> 00:14:58,151
<i>With all due respect, Chancellor,
the Council has a plan in place.</i>

214
00:14:58,610 --> 00:15:00,904
Yes, and so does Moralo Eval,

215
00:15:00,987 --> 00:15:03,365
who appears to be several steps ahead
of you.

216
00:15:03,698 --> 00:15:06,493
For that reason,
I asked Anakin to take action.

217
00:15:06,785 --> 00:15:11,248
<i>He is confident he can find the fugitives
and stop this plot against me.</i>

218
00:15:11,331 --> 00:15:14,793
<i>I suggest you have more faith
in young Skywalker.</i>

219
00:15:16,503 --> 00:15:19,881
<i>Captain, if you must escort me home,
I'm leaving now.</i>

220
00:15:20,340 --> 00:15:21,591
<i>Yes, sir.</i>

221
00:15:22,175 --> 00:15:25,262
This is exactly what Obi-Wan
didn't want to happen.

222
00:15:25,846 --> 00:15:29,307
If I warn him, it could blow his cover,
get him killed.

223
00:15:30,976 --> 00:15:33,437
Kill Hardeen, Skywalker might.

224
00:15:33,520 --> 00:15:35,272
Or die trying, he may.

225
00:15:36,440 --> 00:15:38,150
Warn them both, you must.

226
00:15:38,233 --> 00:15:40,485
Overdue, the truth is.

227
00:15:51,204 --> 00:15:53,123
How do you know
they couldn't have gotten very far?

228
00:15:55,000 --> 00:15:56,710
So you only gave them enough fuel

229
00:15:56,793 --> 00:15:58,712
to reach the nearest filling station
on Orondia,

230
00:15:58,795 --> 00:16:01,423
which is owned by your brother?

231
00:16:01,506 --> 00:16:02,966
Well, that's a nice little
money-making scam.

232
00:16:04,301 --> 00:16:05,552
We better get going.

233
00:16:05,594 --> 00:16:07,429
Orondia's pretty deserted.

234
00:16:07,512 --> 00:16:09,055
They may steal a ship there,

235
00:16:09,097 --> 00:16:10,640
to throw us off their trail.

236
00:16:10,724 --> 00:16:12,517
I like your thinking.

237
00:16:27,908 --> 00:16:31,077
Here, take it. I just want to get out of here.

238
00:16:32,245 --> 00:16:33,580
We're being swindled.

239
00:16:33,622 --> 00:16:37,626
Who sells a ship with only enough fuel
to get to this lousy rock?

240
00:16:38,043 --> 00:16:42,047
The way I see it,
you keep paying off everybody but me.

241
00:16:42,088 --> 00:16:44,341
Yeah, why is that?

242
00:16:58,563 --> 00:16:59,981
Look! It's Cad Bane.

243
00:17:00,106 --> 00:17:01,107
Are you sure?

244
00:17:01,566 --> 00:17:03,485
Ugh, who else wears a hat like that?

245
00:17:03,610 --> 00:17:04,945
Good point.

246
00:17:14,746 --> 00:17:16,039
Now what?

247
00:17:16,540 --> 00:17:17,791
Jedi!

248
00:17:38,937 --> 00:17:41,231
Take over! I'll bring them down!

249
00:17:53,910 --> 00:17:55,579
I'll take care of him.

250
00:17:55,996 --> 00:17:59,207
No! It's my turn to kill a Jedi!

251
00:19:19,329 --> 00:19:20,497
Anakin.

252
00:19:50,110 --> 00:19:52,612
You're going to pay for what you did.

253
00:19:53,238 --> 00:19:54,948
You shouldn't have gotten involved.

254
00:19:58,952 --> 00:20:00,412
This is for Obi-Wan.

255
00:20:02,664 --> 00:20:05,083
You can thank me later, Hardeen.

256
00:20:07,252 --> 00:20:09,963
You had your chance to kill him.

257
00:20:10,046 --> 00:20:11,464
Now it's my turn.

258
00:20:41,369 --> 00:20:44,289
Anakin, don't follow me.

259
00:21:02,474 --> 00:21:04,601
The ship is still operational.

260
00:21:04,684 --> 00:21:07,562
I got it working. Now let's get out of here.

261
00:21:08,188 --> 00:21:10,523
You're lucky we're in a hurry, little lady.

262
00:21:12,525 --> 00:21:14,903
We'll have to dance another time.

263
00:21:20,617 --> 00:21:21,701
Master!

264
00:21:21,993 --> 00:21:24,037
Master, are you all right?

265
00:21:35,882 --> 00:21:38,176
What is it? What's wrong?

266
00:21:38,218 --> 00:21:41,262
That's why I felt a connection.

267
00:21:41,346 --> 00:21:43,556
Obi-Wan is still alive.

268
00:21:43,681 --> 00:21:46,726
-I don't understand.
-I don't, either.

269
00:21:46,768 --> 00:21:50,355
But we're gonna get
to the bottom of this. Believe me.

270
00:21:50,379 --> 00:21:55,379
http://hiqve.com/

